author: HBO Max
description:
Dive into summer with a new episode of DC Studios Showcase, where hosts Frankey Smith, Tyler Coates, and Comic Correspondent Coy Jandreau break down everything from Peacemaker’s fight choreography to blockbuster movie season in the DC Universe. This episode features an exclusive interview with Wayne Dalglish, stunt coordinator for Peacemaker Season 1, who shares insider stories on crafting iconic fight scenes, working with James Gunn, and contributing to major superhero projects like Superman and Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 3. Plus: The hosts talk dream summer vacations in the DCU, the balance of comedy and action in superhero storytelling, and what’s next for the expanding DCU. Subscribe for more deep dives, behind-the-scenes interviews, and exclusive conversations with the people shaping DC’s future.

Wayne Daglish  - Stunt Coordinator

description:
Executive producers Michael Patrick King, Susan Fales-Hill, and Elisa Zuritsky dig into the season three finale with the help of co-executive producer Samantha Irby and executive story editors Lucas Froehlich and Rachel Palmer. This one’s full of behind-the-scenes details, from the inspiration behind Carrie’s futuristic dining companion to the writers’ heated debate over Seema’s jeans. Plus, Michael shares the iconic line from the Sex and the City series finale that he set out to revisit in this episode.
